Date: Tue, 05 Mar 1996 03:11:08 -0800
From: tjh@rfhsm.ac.uk (Dr Tim J Harrison)
Subject: Re: PROMED-EDR: Hepatitis G - Brazil (2)
Formal assignment of the name hepatitis G virus (HGV) awaits the decision of
the International Committee on the Taxonomy of Viruses (ICTV). Meanwhile,
the candidate names GBV-C and HGV have been given to viruses described in
Nature Medicine (1995, 1:564-9) and Science (1996, 271:505-8). The sequences
of the genomes of these viruses are in Genbank (accession numbers U36380 and
U44402) and show 95% amino acid identity (85% at the nucleotide level).
Thus, these seem to be isolates (perhaps different genotypes)of the same
virus. See also the commentary by A J Zuckerman in the current issue of the
Lancet (1996, 347:558-9).
Tim J Harrison PhD MRCPath
Reader in Molecular Virology
Royal Free Hospital School of Medicine
tjh@rfhsm.ac.uk
